nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Culpeper was born about 1482, in Bedgebury, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with John Saint Clere. She died about 1532, at the age of 52."},"et":{"about 1482–about 1532":"umbes 1482–umbes 1532","1478–1574":"1478–1574","1530–1574":"1530–1574","1482–1532":"1482–1532","1478":"1478","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1574":"1574","about 1532":"umbes 1532","1482":"1482","About 1530":"umbes 1530","about 1482":"umbes 1482","St Osyth, Tendring District, Essex, England":"St Osyth, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bedgebury, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Bedgebury, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bedgebury, Kent, England, Great Britian":"Bedgebury, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1482–about 1532":"noin 1482–noin 1532","1478–1574":"1478–1574","1530–1574":"1530–1574","1482–1532":"1482–1532","1478":"1478","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1574":"1574","about 1532":"noin 1532","1482":"1482","About 1530":"noin 1530","about 1482":"noin 1482","St Osyth, Tendring District, Essex, England":"St Osyth, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bedgebury, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Bedgebury, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bedgebury, Kent, England, Great Britian":"Bedgebury, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1482–about 1532":"environ 1482–environ 1532","1478–1574":"1478–1574